The paper deals with the scaling laws of signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) and area spectral efficiency (ASE) in multi-antenna cellular networks. This involves the study of information theory, networking, and communication systems, which are all covered by the arXiv categories cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.COM. The paper also discusses the use of multiple antennas for beamforming, which falls under the category of cs.MM (multi-agent systems and game theory). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of dense cellular networks, which is covered by the category cs.SI (social and information networks).
